\How to Play\ \Setup\ \ The game is for 2\-10 players\, ages 7 and over\. Every player starts with seven cards\, and they are dealt face down\. The rest of the cards are placed in a Draw Pile face down\. Next to the pile a space should be designated for a Discard Pile\. The top card should be placed in the Discard Pile\, and the game begins\! \ \Game Play\ \ The aim of the game is to be the first player to score 500 points\, achieved \(usually over several rounds of play\) by a player discarding all of their cards and earning points corresponding to the value of the remaining cards still held by the other players\. Action cards \(Skip\, Draw Two and Reverse\) are worth 20 Points while Wild and Wild Draw Four cards are worth 50 Points\. \ \ To start a hand\, seven cards are dealt to each player\, with the top card of the deck flipped over and set aside to begin the discard pile\. \ \
